<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:mediaobject>
<db:imageobject>
<db:imagedata fileref="images/effect_motion_blur.png"/>
</db:imageobject>
</db:mediaobject>
<db:para>The <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-effects-motionblur.xml">MotionBlur</db:link> effect creates a trailing streak for rapidly moving objects in the scene.</db:para>
<db:note>
<db:para>The <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-sceneenvironment.xml#backgroundMode-prop">background mode</db:link> must be <db:code>SceneEnvironment.Transparent</db:code> for <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-effects-motionblur.xml">MotionBlur</db:link> to work.</db:para>
</db:note>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="property-documentation">
<db:title>Property Documentation</db:title>
<db:section xml:id="blurQuality-prop">
<db:title>blurQuality : real</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>real</db:type>
<db:varname>blurQuality</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>The quality of the blur used to create the trail. Increasing quality will have impact on performance. The range is <db:code>[0...1]</db:code>. The default value is <db:code>0.25</db:code>.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="fadeAmount-prop">
<db:title>fadeAmount : real</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>real</db:type>
<db:varname>fadeAmount</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>How fast the trail fades. The range is <db:code>[0...1]</db:code>, with <db:code>0</db:code> meaning that the object trail persists indefinitely, and <db:code>1</db:code> meaning that the object trail fades out immediately. The default value is <db:code>0.25</db:code>.</db:para>
</db:section>
</db:section>
